summary: Eileen Gail Dinneen was an employee of the U.S. House of Representatives Select Committee on Assassinations (HSCA). The documents available are certification reports and payroll certifications that list her position and salary during the period from May to November 1978. These documents provide administrative details about her employment within the HSCA, but do not specify her exact role or responsibilities within the committee's investigation.
significance: Eileen Gail Dinneen's significance lies in her employment with the HSCA, indicating her involvement in the investigation of the JFK assassination, although the specific nature and impact of her role are not detailed in these documents.
